ion/style-rules#nesting">nested rules</a>, <a href="/documentation/at-rules/mixin">mixins</a>, <a href="/documentation/modules">functions</a>, and more, all with a fully CSS-compatible syntax. Sass helps keep large stylesheets well-organized and makes it easy to share design within and across projects.</p> </div> <ul> <li><p>If you&rsquo;re looking for an introduction to Sass, check out <a href="/guide">the tutorial</a>.</p></li> <li><p>If you want to look up a built-in Sass function, look no further than <a href="/documentation/modules">the built-in module reference</a>.</p></li> <li><p>If you&rsquo;re calling Sass from JavaScript, you may want the <a href="https://github.com/sass/node-sass#usage"><span class=caps>JS</span>&nbsp;<span class=caps>API</span> documentation</a>.</p></li> <li><p>Or the <a href="https://pub.dartlang.org/documentation/sass/latest/sass/sass-library.html">Dart <span class=caps>API</span> documentation</a> if you&rsquo;re calling it from&nbsp;Dart.</p></li> <li><p>Otherwise, use the table of contents for the language&nbsp;reference!</p></li> </ul> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> <div class=sl-c-alert> <div aria-labelledby=release-nav class='sl-l-container sl-c-list-horizontal-wrapper'> <ul class=sl-l-grid--justify-center> <li id=release-nav> Current Releases: </li> <li> <span class=release-name><a href="/dart-sass">Dart Sass</a>&#32;<a href="https://github.com/sass/dart-sass/releases/tag/1.24.4">1.24.4</a></span> </li> <li> <span class=release-name><a href="/libsass">LibSass</a>&#32;<a href="https://github.com/sass/libsass/releases/tag/3.6.3">3.6.3</a></span> </li> <li> <span class=release-name><a href="/ruby-sass">Ruby Sass</a><span aria-label=coffin role=presentation> &#32; âš° </span></span> </li> <li class='sl-l-grid__column sl-l-large-grid__column--auto-size'> <a href="/implementation">Implementation Guide</a> </li> </ul> </div> </div> </main> <footer class='site-footer contentinfo' itemscope=itemscope itemtype='